#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.7:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Dhanavagga"
msgstr "1. Wealth"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 7. Uggasutta → uggamahāmaggasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Uggasutta"
msgstr "7. With Ugga"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.7:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uggo rājamahāmatto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uggo "
"rājamahāmatto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Ugga the government minister went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to "
"one side, and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.7:2.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an7.7:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yāva aḍḍho cāyaṃ, bhante, migāro rohaṇeyyo yāva mahaddhano yāva mahābhogo”ti."
msgstr "Migāra of Rohaṇa is so rich, so very wealthy.”"

msgctxt "an7.7:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Kīva aḍḍho panugga, migāro rohaṇeyyo, kīva mahaddhano, kīva mahābhogo”ti?"
msgstr "“But Ugga, how rich is he?”"

# BB’s “units of minted gold” is a terribly artificial idiom for a common term. Despite occurring frequently, there is little in the suttas to distinguish hiranna from suvanna. However Mnd 1 says hiraññaṃ vuccati kahāpaṇoti. On the whole, suvanna seems to be used widely for natural gold and golden things, hiranna is less common and is most characteristically used, as here, when reckoning wealth, eg Cīvaracetāpannaṃ nāma hiraññaṃ vā suvaṇṇaṃ vā muttā vā maṇi vā; Natthi me, āvuso, hiraññassa paṭivīso, nāhaṃ hiraññaṃ sādiyāmī; Khettaṃ vatthuṃ hiraññaṃ vā, gavāssaṃ dāsaporisaṃ; Asīti sakaṭavāhānaṃ, hiraññassa ahosi me; Pahūtaṃ me jātarūpaṃ, muttā veḷuriyā; Vaṇijjā tādisī natthi, hiraññena kayākayaṃ; Na pasū brāhmaṇānāsuṃ, na hiraññaṃ na dhāniyaṃ. However, also consider the Hirannavati River, i.e. river with gold (nuggets or dust).
#. VAR: satasahassānaṃ → sahassānaṃ (bj) | sahassāni (s1-3) | satasahassāni (?)
msgctxt "an7.7:2.4"
msgid "“Sataṃ, bhante, satasahassānaṃ hiraññassa, ko pana vādo rūpiyassā”ti."
msgstr "“He has a hundred thousand gold coins, not to mention the silver!”"

msgctxt "an7.7:2.5"
msgid "“Atthi kho etaṃ, ugga, dhanaṃ netaṃ ‘natthī’ti vadāmīti."
msgstr "“Well, Ugga, that is wealth, I can’t deny it."

msgctxt "an7.7:2.6"
msgid ""
"Tañca kho etaṃ, ugga, dhanaṃ sādhāraṇaṃ agginā udakena rājūhi corehi "
"appiyehi dāyādehi."
msgstr ""
"But fire, water, rulers, thieves, and unloved heirs all take a share of that "
"wealth."

msgctxt "an7.7:2.7"
msgid ""
"Satta kho imāni, ugga, dhanāni asādhāraṇāni agginā udakena rājūhi corehi "
"appiyehi dāyādehi."
msgstr "There are these seven kinds of wealth that they can’t take a share of."

msgctxt "an7.7:2.8"
msgid "Katamāni satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "an7.7:2.9"
msgid ""
"Saddhādhanaṃ, sīladhanaṃ, hirīdhanaṃ, ottappadhanaṃ, sutadhanaṃ, cāgadhanaṃ, "
"paññādhanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The wealth of faith, ethical conduct, conscience, prudence, learning, "
"generosity, and wisdom."

msgctxt "an7.7:2.10"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, ugga, satta dhanāni asādhāraṇāni agginā udakena rājūhi corehi "
"appiyehi dāyādehīti."
msgstr ""
"There are these seven kinds of wealth that fire, water, rulers, thieves, and "
"unloved heirs can’t take a share of.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an7.7:3.1"
msgid "Saddhādhanaṃ sīladhanaṃ,"
msgstr "“Faith and ethical conduct are kinds of wealth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:3.2"
msgid "hirī ottappiyaṃ dhanaṃ;"
msgstr "as are conscience and prudence,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:3.3"
msgid "Sutadhanañca cāgo ca,"
msgstr "learning and generosity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:3.4"
msgid "paññā ve sattamaṃ dhanaṃ."
msgstr "and wisdom is the seventh kind of wealth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an7.7:4.1"
msgid "Yassa ete dhanā atthi,"
msgstr "When a woman or man"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:4.2"
msgid "itthiyā purisassa vā;"
msgstr "has these kinds of wealth,"

# BB says these verses are identical with AN 7.5, however these two lines are different.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:4.3"
msgid "Sa ve mahaddhano loke,"
msgstr "they’re really rich in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:4.4"
msgid "ajeyyo devamānuse."
msgstr "invincible among gods and humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an7.7:5.1"
msgid "Tasmā saddhañca sīlañca,"
msgstr "And so a clever person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:5.2"
msgid "pasādaṃ dhammadassanaṃ;"
msgstr "remembering the Buddha’s instructions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:5.3"
msgid "Anuyuñjetha medhāvī,"
msgstr "should be committed to faith and ethical conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an7.7:5.4"
msgid "saraṃ buddhāna sāsanan”ti."
msgstr "confidence, and seeing the truth.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.7:5.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
